WEBVTT



00:00:00.832 --> 00:00:05.952
Well, hello, friends, and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's Holy Word.

00:00:05.696 --> 00:00:08.352
Today we're reading Mark chapter 8.

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:12.960
And in this lesson we are invited to think about how we see Jesus

00:00:12.768 --> 00:00:16.608
And seeing him how we see ourselves.

00:00:16.832 --> 00:00:18.752
Before we read, let's pray.

00:00:18.944 --> 00:00:22.528
Our Father in heaven, give us eyes to see.

00:00:22.592 --> 00:00:24.448
In Jesus' name I ask.

00:00:24.640 --> 00:00:25.792
Amen.

00:00:26.336 --> 00:00:28.064
Mark, chapter eight.

00:00:28.864 --> 00:00:34.528
In those days, when again a great crowd had gathered and they had nothing to eat,

00:00:34.336 --> 00:00:37.984
He called his disciples to him and said to them,

00:00:37.728 --> 00:00:44.672
I have compassion on the crowd because they have been with me now three days and have nothing to eat.

00:00:44.736 --> 00:00:49.088
And if I send them away hungry to their homes, they will faint.

00:00:48.928 --> 00:00:50.304
On the way.

00:00:50.528 --> 00:00:53.344
And some of them have come from far away.

00:00:53.760 --> 00:01:00.448
And his disciples answered him, How can one feed these people with bread here in this desolate place?

00:01:00.064 --> 00:01:03.712
And he asked them, how many loaves do you have?

00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:04.864
They said,

00:01:04.928 --> 00:01:06.048
seven.

00:01:06.144 --> 00:01:09.728
And he directed the crowd to sit down on the ground.

00:01:09.536 --> 00:01:13.312
And he took the seven loaves, and having given thanks,

00:01:13.056 --> 00:01:21.344
He broke them and gave them to his disciples to set before the people, and they set them before the crowd, and they had a few small fish.

00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:26.720
And having blessed them, he said that these also should be set before them.

00:01:26.656 --> 00:01:27.776
And they ate.

00:01:27.808 --> 00:01:29.376
And were satisfied.

00:01:29.216 --> 00:01:33.920
Then they took up the broken pieces left over, seven baskets full.

00:01:33.568 --> 00:01:36.608
And there were about 4,000 people.

00:01:36.672 --> 00:01:38.432
And he sent them away.

00:01:38.464 --> 00:01:44.064
And immediately he got into the boat with his disciples, and went to the district of Dalmanutha.

00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:51.840
The Pharisees came and began to argue with him, seeking from him a sign from heaven to test him.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.256
And he sighed deeply in his spirit and said,

00:01:55.904 --> 00:01:59.520
Why does this generation seek a sign?

00:01:59.552 --> 00:02:03.936
Truly, I say to you, no sign will be given to this generation.

00:02:04.032 --> 00:02:05.440
And he left them.

00:02:05.312 --> 00:02:07.040
Got into the boat again.

00:02:06.848 --> 00:02:08.960
And went to the other side

00:02:09.088 --> 00:02:14.016
Now they had forgotten to bring bread and they had only one loaf with them in the boat.

00:02:13.888 --> 00:02:17.248
And he cautioned them saying, "Watch out!"

00:02:17.120 --> 00:02:21.344
Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and the leaven of Herod.

00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:26.752
And they began discussing with one another the fact that they had no bread.

00:02:26.784 --> 00:02:29.760
And Jesus, aware of this, said to them,

00:02:29.504 --> 00:02:32.864
Why are you discussing the fact that you have no bread?

00:02:32.768 --> 00:02:36.224
Do you not yet perceive or understand?

00:02:35.968 --> 00:02:37.792
Are your hearts hardened?

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:44.096
Having eyes, do you not see? And having ears, do you not hear? And do you not remember?

00:02:44.224 --> 00:02:51.456
when i broke the five loaves for the five thousand how many baskets full of broken pieces did you take up?

00:02:51.712 --> 00:02:53.440
They said to him,

00:02:53.408 --> 00:02:54.496
Twelve.

00:02:54.496 --> 00:02:57.280
And the seven for the four thousand.

00:02:56.992 --> 00:02:58.304
How many basket?

00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.120
It's full of broken pieces. Did you take up?

00:03:01.216 --> 00:03:02.656
And they said to him,

00:03:02.592 --> 00:03:03.680
Seven.

00:03:03.872 --> 00:03:05.376
And he said to them,

00:03:05.312 --> 00:03:07.104
Do you not understand?

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:18.208
And they came to Bethsaida, and some people brought to him a blind man, and begging him to touch him, and he took the blind man by the hand and led him out of the village.

00:03:17.728 --> 00:03:23.552
And when he had spent on his eyes and laid his hands on him, he asked him, do you see anything? Do you see anything?

00:03:23.552 --> 00:03:28.352
And he looked up and said, I see people, but they look like trees walking.

00:03:28.576 --> 00:03:36.224
Then Jesus laid his hands on his eyes again, and he opened his eyes. His sight was restored, and he saw everything clearly.

00:03:36.576 --> 00:03:39.040
And he sent him to his home, saying,

00:03:38.848 --> 00:03:40.800
Do not even enter the village.

00:03:41.152 --> 00:03:50.560
And Jesus went on with his disciples to the villages of Caesarea Philippi, and on the way he asked his disciples, Who do people say that I am?

00:03:50.528 --> 00:03:51.840
And they told him.

00:03:51.648 --> 00:03:53.056
John the Baptist.

00:03:52.864 --> 00:03:54.816
But others say, Elijah.

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:56.704
And others, one of the prophets,

00:03:56.576 --> 00:04:01.056
And he asked them, But who do you say that I am?

00:04:01.056 --> 00:04:02.592
Peter answered him,

00:04:02.432 --> 00:04:04.704
You are the Christ.

00:04:04.864 --> 00:04:08.032
And he strictly charged them to tell no one about him.

00:04:07.744 --> 00:04:17.792
And he began to teach them that the son of Man must suffer many things, and be rejected by the elders and the chief priests and the scribes, and be.

00:04:17.312 --> 00:04:21.248
and be killed, and after three days rise again. Amen.

00:04:21.056 --> 00:04:23.232
And he said this plainly.

00:04:23.264 --> 00:04:26.240
And Peter took him aside and began to rebuke him.

00:04:26.432 --> 00:04:32.704
But turning and seeing his disciples, he rebuked Peter and said, Get behind me, Satan.

00:04:32.512 --> 00:04:35.648
For you are not setting your mind on the things of God.

00:04:35.488 --> 00:04:37.280
But on the things of man.

00:04:37.504 --> 00:04:47.552
And calling the crowd to him with his disciples, he said to them, If anyone would come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

00:04:47.072 --> 00:04:47.968
Follow me.

00:04:47.968 --> 00:04:52.000
For whoever would save his life will lose it.

00:04:51.936 --> 00:04:57.568
But whoever loses his life for my sake and the gospels will save it.

00:04:57.408 --> 00:05:01.056
For what does it profit a man to gain the whole world?

00:05:00.864 --> 00:05:02.944
And forfeit his soul.

00:05:03.168 --> 00:05:06.880
For what can a man give in return for his soul?

00:05:07.104 --> 00:05:17.152
For whoever is ashamed of me, and of my words, in this adulterous and sinful generation of him, will the son of Man also be ashamed when he comes?

00:05:17.088 --> 00:05:19.520
In the glory of his father.

00:05:19.456 --> 00:05:21.280
With the holy angels.

00:05:22.304 --> 00:05:23.424
Amen.

00:05:23.360 --> 00:05:25.248
This is God's Word.

00:05:25.856 --> 00:05:32.768
Jesus here again feeds the hungry thousands and again gives sight to the blind.

00:05:32.384 --> 00:05:42.432
How kind is his compassion? He meets our needs. How great is his power? Nothing is too hard for him. Yet, how hard hard

00:05:41.952 --> 00:05:43.264
Hard-hearted

00:05:43.008 --> 00:05:45.888
are the Pharisees. They won't trust him.

00:05:45.600 --> 00:05:55.648
They won't believe he is who he is. Even the disciples are slow to understand. They're in danger of getting infected.

00:05:55.168 --> 00:06:05.216
The infected, so to speak, with the unbelief of the Pharisees, like a whole loaf of bread gets leavened. That leaven is what makes bread go rise. It evolves.

00:06:04.736 --> 00:06:14.784
It involves chemical reactions with yeast or gluten or baking soda that spreads throughout the whole bread dough, causing little gas bubbles. And as a

00:06:14.304 --> 00:06:23.392
And as it bakes, the gas gets hot and expands and causes the bread to rise, much like air blows up a balloon.

00:06:23.552 --> 00:06:29.888
Jesus warns us the Pharisees have a leaven of unbelief.

00:06:29.984 --> 00:06:33.280
they want Jesus to prove himself

00:06:33.088 --> 00:06:43.136
to be the Messiah by doing miracles or signs like a circus monkey performing tricks to entertain. Yet Jesus did do miracles.

00:06:42.656 --> 00:06:43.456
course.

00:06:43.328 --> 00:06:48.512
and he fed four thousand and he healed a blind man yet they won't believe.

00:06:48.224 --> 00:06:58.272
that that last miracle is interesting it was done in stages not all at once but over time and as a kind of parable for us this is how

00:06:57.792 --> 00:07:06.560
This is how people come to believe Jesus is the Messiah. This is how the Holy Spirit works in our lives. First, we are blind.

00:07:06.464 --> 00:07:16.512
then we begin to see but not distinctly and then we have greater clarity and see jesus for who he really is and in heaven we'll see him in.

00:07:16.032 --> 00:07:17.376
him even better.

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:22.848
that Peter began to see and said, "You are the Christ."

00:07:22.624 --> 00:07:24.064
The Messiah.

00:07:23.744 --> 00:07:26.880
Now, how did Peter get eyes to see Jesus correctly?

00:07:26.784 --> 00:07:36.832
Well, the Gospel of Matthew tells us, Jesus said to Peter, "Blessed are you, Simon Bar-Jonah, for flesh and blood has not revealed this to you.

00:07:36.352 --> 00:07:36.928
you.

00:07:36.672 --> 00:07:38.880
But my father who is in heaven.

00:07:39.232 --> 00:07:44.640
Peter got eyes to see just like the blind man did. He got them from God.

00:07:44.416 --> 00:07:52.576
God the Son gave the blind man sight. God the Father revealed Peter, God the Son.

00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:56.480
And so it is with us. When we finally see that Jesus died,

00:07:56.096 --> 00:08:03.264
It is the Messiah. It is because God, the Holy Spirit, gives us eyes to see.

00:08:03.392 --> 00:08:06.752
So Jesus says, now that you know who I am,

00:08:06.848 --> 00:08:09.536
Let me tell you what I'm going to do.

00:08:09.632 --> 00:08:11.360
I'm going to suffer.

00:08:11.264 --> 00:08:12.800
Be rejected.

00:08:12.608 --> 00:08:13.888
Die!

00:08:13.664 --> 00:08:15.168
And rise again.

00:08:15.584 --> 00:08:18.464
Now Peter shows that he sees

00:08:18.272 --> 00:08:20.224
But not clearly enough.

00:08:20.192 --> 00:08:24.128
For he rebukes Jesus privately, saying to him, never, Lord.

00:08:23.904 --> 00:08:26.816
You're the Messiah, so you must not die.

00:08:26.784 --> 00:08:30.912
Jesus says, "I'm the Messiah and so I must."

00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:35.104
And to say I must not is to think like Satan,

00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:40.512
Not like God. Get behind me, he says, for I must die.

00:08:40.736 --> 00:08:45.024
Because that is how I will rescue my people from their sins.

00:08:45.728 --> 00:08:55.776
now if we have come to believe that jesus is the messiah and that jesus has died for our sins and got raised to him from the dead how should we see

00:08:55.296 --> 00:08:56.576
We see God.

00:08:56.384 --> 00:08:57.920
Ourselves.

00:08:58.048 --> 00:08:59.616
Jesus says,

00:08:59.392 --> 00:09:00.512
Follow me.

00:09:00.736 --> 00:09:03.584
Deny yourself and take up your cross

00:09:03.328 --> 00:09:04.896
And follow me.

00:09:05.152 --> 00:09:13.440
Someone carrying a cross upon which a person would be crucified was someone whose life as they knew it was over.

00:09:14.336 --> 00:09:16.224
We are to take up

00:09:16.192 --> 00:09:22.592
the cross and consider ourselves dead to this world but alive to Christ

00:09:22.176 --> 00:09:30.336
"'Dead to our old way of living, "'but now to walk in newness of life "'with Christ and to serve Christ, "'why would we not?'

00:09:30.432 --> 00:09:33.888
What is there left for us in the old life?

00:09:33.824 --> 00:09:38.432
Nothing, Jesus says, for whoever would save his life will lose it.

00:09:38.592 --> 00:09:42.752
But whoever loses his life for my sake and the gospels

00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:43.904
We'll save it.

00:09:44.288 --> 00:09:46.464
So, don't be a fool.

00:09:46.304 --> 00:09:49.920
and reject Jesus. I think you'll end up with anything here.

00:09:50.144 --> 00:09:54.240
Or imagine that you could buy your soul out of hell.

00:09:54.528 --> 00:09:56.768
If you end up there.

00:09:56.928 --> 00:10:00.640
For what does it profit a man, says Jesus, to gain the whole world?

00:10:00.416 --> 00:10:04.320
And forfeit his soul, for what can a man give in exchange?

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:06.400
Or in return for his soul.

00:10:06.304 --> 00:10:11.456
No, the thing to do is to embrace Jesus as your Messiah.

00:10:11.616 --> 00:10:15.200
And then begin to live for him, even if others won't.

00:10:15.456 --> 00:10:23.936
For whoever is ashamed of me, says Jesus, and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation of him, will the son of Man also be ashamed.

00:10:23.744 --> 00:10:26.112
When he comes in the glory of his father.

00:10:25.888 --> 00:10:27.616
with the holy angels.

00:10:27.744 --> 00:10:31.904
As another said, he who he is no fool.

00:10:31.840 --> 00:10:33.184
Who gives?

00:10:32.928 --> 00:10:34.688
What he cannot keep,

00:10:34.752 --> 00:10:37.984
To gain what he cannot lose.

00:10:38.400 --> 00:10:39.680
Let's pray.

00:10:39.904 --> 00:10:44.576
Father in heaven, thank you for Jesus the Messiah upon his life.

00:10:44.512 --> 00:10:46.368
A life that he lived.

00:10:46.272 --> 00:10:49.344
And upon his death, a death that he died,

00:10:49.248 --> 00:10:51.360
we seek our whole eternity.

00:10:51.616 --> 00:10:53.152
Help us then,

00:10:52.928 --> 00:10:55.296
To live for him who died for us.

00:10:55.232 --> 00:10:56.800
In Jesus name

00:10:56.960 --> 00:10:58.016
Amen.

00:10:57.952 --> 00:11:01.184
Well, thank you for listening in, and I hope you'll join me next time.
